27/04/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Deputy Chief of the Bulgarian Army's General Staff, Lt Gen Zlatan Stoykov, arrived in BiH on Friday (25 April) to visit SFOR's 3rd Guard Company in Camp Butmir, which includes 142 Bulgarian troops.
The servicemen in Butmir will be given career service positions in the Bulgarian armed forces as of 1 June.
Sofia sent personnel to the international mission in Afghanistan and plans to send a unit to Iraq next month.
(BTA - 25/04/03)
